SIMPLE: irriguous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irriguous
<hw>Ir*rig"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>irriguus</ets>. See <er>Irrigate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Watered; watery; moist; dewy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flowery lap⟦br⟧
Of some <qex>irriguous</qex> valley spreads her store.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gently penetrating or pervading.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>J. Philips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irrisible</ent>⟦br⟧
